Note:
==============================================================================
COMMITMENT - Pedersen and hash-based cryptographic commitments
==============================================================================

A commitment scheme is a protocol where a committer publishes a commitment
to a value v without revealing v, then later opens (reveals) v together with
a blinding factor r. The scheme has two properties:

  - Hiding: the commitment reveals nothing about v (information-theoretic
    for Pedersen, computational for hash-based).
  - Binding: the committer cannot open the commitment to two different
    values (computational for Pedersen via the discrete log assumption,
    information-theoretic for hash-based via collision resistance of SHA-256).

This module provides:

  - pedersen_commit(value, blinding) -> Commitment = v*G + r*H
    where G is the Ed25519 basepoint and H is an independent generator
    derived deterministically from SHA-256("Runa-Pedersen-Ed25519-Generator").

  - pedersen_verify(commitment, value, blinding) -> 1 / 0
    Recompute the commitment and constant-time compare.

  - pedersen_add(c1, c2) -> homomorphic add: commit(v1+v2, r1+r2) = c1 + c2.

  - hash_commit(value, blinding) -> SHA-256(blinding || value)
  - hash_verify(commitment, value, blinding) -> 1 / 0

References:
- Pedersen, "Non-Interactive and Information-Theoretic Secure Verifiable
  Secret Sharing", CRYPTO 1991.
- RFC 8032: Ed25519 group operations.
- FIPS 180-4: SHA-256.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/secure_memory.runa" as Secure
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/ed25519.runa" as Ed25519
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/sha2.runa" as Sha2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 1: Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Let COMMITMENT_POINT_SIZE be 32
Let COMMITMENT_SCALAR_SIZE be 32
Let COMMITMENT_HASH_SIZE be 32

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 2: H generator derivation
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
The Pedersen scheme requires a second generator H whose discrete log
relative to G is unknown to anyone. We derive H by hashing a fixed
domain-separation string and decompressing the result as an Ed25519 point.

If the decompression fails (the hash output doesn't lie on the curve), we
increment a counter and rehash; this is the standard "try-and-increment"
hash-to-curve technique. For the Ed25519 curve about half of all 32-byte
values are on the curve, so the expected number of attempts is 2.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Build seed string: "Runa-Pedersen-Ed25519-Generator" + counter byte.
  2. Hash with SHA-256 to get 32 bytes.
  3. Try to decompress as Ed25519 compressed point.
  4. If decompression fails, increment counter and retry.
  5. To produce a prime-order generator, multiply the resulting point by
     the cofactor (8 for Ed25519) so the result is in the prime-order
     subgroup.
  6. Cache result for the lifetime of the arena.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(expected_attempts) point decompressions; ~2 on average. The cofactor
multiplication is a single scalar-mult.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
H is public material. The construction is verifiable: anyone can re-run
the hash-to-curve and check they get the same H.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "commitment_derive_h_generator" takes arena as Integer, out_point_xyzt as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Build the domain-separation seed: a 32-byte SHA-256 of a fixed string.
    Note: Domain: ASCII bytes "Runa-Pedersen-Ed25519-Generator\x00" (32 bytes total
    Note: including the trailing counter byte). On retry we bump the counter.
    Let seed_buf be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    If seed_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Fill with the ASCII domain-separation string, padded with the counter.
    Note: "Runa-Pedersen-Ed25519-Generator" is 31 bytes; the 32nd byte is the counter.
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 0, 82)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 1, 117)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 2, 110)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 3, 97)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 4, 45)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 5, 80)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 6, 101)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 7, 100)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 8, 101)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 9, 114)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 10, 115)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 11, 101)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 12, 110)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 13, 45)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 14, 69)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 15, 100)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 16, 50)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 17, 53)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 18, 53)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 19, 49)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 20, 57)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 21, 45)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 22, 71)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 23, 101)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 24, 110)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 25, 101)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 26, 114)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 27, 97)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 28, 116)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 29, 111)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 30, 114)
    Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 31, 0)

    Let attempt be 0
    Let max_attempts be 64
    Let candidate be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    If candidate is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    While attempt is less than max_attempts:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(seed_buf, 31, attempt)
        Let rc be Sha2.sha256_hash(arena, seed_buf, 32, candidate)
        If rc is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Note: Force the compressed-point sign bit to zero. RFC 8032 5.1.2
        Note: defines the high bit of byte 31 as the sign of x; clearing it
        Note: selects the even-y representative, which is the canonical
        Note: compressed form. This halves the search space of candidate
        Note: points and yields a deterministic-on-seed H independent of
        Note: the upper bit of the SHA-256 digest.
        Let candidate_31 be Memory.memory_get_byte(candidate, 31)
        Let candidate_31_cleared be candidate_31 bitwise_and 127
        Memory.memory_set_byte(candidate, 31, candidate_31_cleared)
        Let dec_rc be Ed25519.ed25519_point_decompress(arena, out_point_xyzt, candidate)
        If dec_rc is equal to 1:
            Note: Multiply by the cofactor (8) to land in the prime-order subgroup.
            Note: Doing this as three doublings is one option; we use scalar mul
            Note: with the byte representation of 8.
            Let cofactor_scalar be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
            If cofactor_scalar is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let z be 0
            While z is less than 32:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(cofactor_scalar, z, 0)
                Set z to z plus 1
            End While
            Memory.memory_set_byte(cofactor_scalar, 0, 8)
            Let cofactor_result be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
            If cofactor_result is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let mul_rc be Ed25519.ed25519_scalarmult(arena, cofactor_result, cofactor_scalar, out_point_xyzt)
            If mul_rc is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Ed25519.ed25519_point_copy(out_point_xyzt, cofactor_result)
            Return 1
        End If
        Set attempt to attempt plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 3: pedersen_commit - compute C = v*G + r*H
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Pedersen commitment over Ed25519. Both value and blinding are 32-byte
little-endian scalars (per RFC 8032 scalar encoding). The commitment is
returned as a 32-byte compressed Ed25519 point.

Returns 0 on failure (e.g., out-of-memory, point operation failure).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Allocate temporary point handles for v*G, r*H, and the sum.
  2. Load the Ed25519 basepoint G.
  3. Compute v*G via scalar-mult.
  4. Derive H and compute r*H via scalar-mult.
  5. Sum P = v*G + r*H using ed25519_point_add.
  6. Compress P to 32 bytes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(scalar_mult * 2 + point_add). Two scalar multiplications dominate.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The blinding scalar is secret; the value may or may not be secret per
application policy. The output point is public.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pedersen_commit" takes arena as Integer, value_scalar_32 as Integer, blinding_scalar_32 as Integer, out_commitment_32 as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value_scalar_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If blinding_scalar_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_commitment_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let g_point be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If g_point is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc_g be Ed25519.ed25519_load_basepoint(arena, g_point)
    If rc_g is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let h_point be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If h_point is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc_h be commitment_derive_h_generator(arena, h_point)
    If rc_h is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let vG be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If vG is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mul1 be Ed25519.ed25519_scalarmult(arena, vG, value_scalar_32, g_point)
    If mul1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let rH be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If rH is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mul2 be Ed25519.ed25519_scalarmult(arena, rH, blinding_scalar_32, h_point)
    If mul2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let sum_point be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If sum_point is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc_add be Ed25519.ed25519_point_add(arena, sum_point, vG, rH)
    If rc_add is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let rc_compress be Ed25519.ed25519_point_compress(arena, sum_point, out_commitment_32)
    If rc_compress is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 4: pedersen_verify - check C == v*G + r*H
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Verify a Pedersen commitment by recomputing v*G + r*H and constant-time
comparing the 32-byte compressed representation against the candidate.

Returns 1 on match, 0 on mismatch (or on error).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Calls pedersen_commit to recompute, then constant_time_compare on the
32 result bytes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Same as pedersen_commit + a 32-byte CT compare.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The CT compare prevents a partial-match timing channel.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pedersen_verify" takes arena as Integer, commitment_32 as Integer, value_scalar_32 as Integer, blinding_scalar_32 as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If commitment_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let recomputed be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    If recomputed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc be pedersen_commit(arena, value_scalar_32, blinding_scalar_32, recomputed)
    If rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Secure.constant_time_compare(recomputed, commitment_32, 32)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 5: pedersen_add - homomorphic addition
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
The Pedersen scheme is additively homomorphic:
  pedersen_commit(v1, r1) + pedersen_commit(v2, r2)
    = (v1*G + r1*H) + (v2*G + r2*H)
    = (v1+v2)*G + (r1+r2)*H
    = pedersen_commit(v1+v2, r1+r2)

This proc adds two commitment points and returns the result as a new
compressed 32-byte point. The caller separately combines the scalars
(v1+v2, r1+r2) for the recipient's verify.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Steps:
  1. Decompress both commitments.
  2. Add the points via ed25519_point_add.
  3. Compress the result.

If either decompression fails (malformed commitment), return 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(2 * decompress + 1 * point_add + 1 * compress). Decompression includes
a square-root in F_p which dominates.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Public point-arithmetic operations.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "pedersen_add" takes arena as Integer, c1_32 as Integer, c2_32 as Integer, out_sum_32 as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If c1_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If c2_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_sum_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p1 be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If p1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc1 be Ed25519.ed25519_point_decompress(arena, p1, c1_32)
    If rc1 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let p2 be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If p2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc2 be Ed25519.ed25519_point_decompress(arena, p2, c2_32)
    If rc2 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sum_point be Ed25519.ed25519_point_alloc(arena)
    If sum_point is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc_add be Ed25519.ed25519_point_add(arena, sum_point, p1, p2)
    If rc_add is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Ed25519.ed25519_point_compress(arena, sum_point, out_sum_32)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 6: hash_commit - SHA-256(blinding || value)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Hash-based commitment using SHA-256 over (blinding || value). This is
the simplest computational binding/computational hiding commitment.

Binding is from SHA-256 collision resistance (computationally infeasible
to find two (v1, r1) (v2, r2) with v1 != v2 and SHA-256(r1||v1) ==
SHA-256(r2||v2) per Wang et al. 2005 lower bounds).

Hiding requires the blinding factor to be a uniformly random 32-byte
value drawn from a cryptographically secure source; with 256 bits of
entropy the search space is infeasible.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Concatenate blinding (32 bytes) and value bytes into a single buffer,
then run SHA-256. Caller supplies blinding from entropy.runa.

Output buffer must be at least 32 bytes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(value_length / 64) SHA-256 compressions; effectively constant for
short values.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The blinding factor is secret and MUST be cryptographically random.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hash_commit" takes arena as Integer, value_bytes as Integer, value_length as Integer, blinding_32 as Integer, out_commitment_32 as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value_bytes is equal to 0:
        If value_length is not equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    If blinding_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_commitment_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let combined be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32 plus value_length)
    If combined is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_copy(combined, blinding_32, 32)
    If value_length is greater than 0:
        Memory.memory_copy(combined plus 32, value_bytes, value_length)
    End If
    Let rc be Sha2.sha256_hash(arena, combined, 32 plus value_length, out_commitment_32)
    Note: Wipe the combined scratch (the blinding portion is secret).
    Secure.secure_zero(combined, 32 plus value_length)
    Return rc
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 7: hash_verify - check SHA-256(blinding || value) == commitment
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Verify a hash-based commitment by recomputing and constant-time comparing.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Recompute via hash_commit into a scratch buffer, then CT compare.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Same as hash_commit + 32-byte CT compare.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
CT compare prevents partial-prefix timing leakage.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "hash_verify" takes arena as Integer, commitment_32 as Integer, value_bytes as Integer, value_length as Integer, blinding_32 as Integer returns Integer:
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If commitment_32 is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let recomputed be Arena.arena_allocate(arena, 32)
    If recomputed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rc be hash_commit(arena, value_bytes, value_length, blinding_32, recomputed)
    If rc is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Secure.constant_time_compare(recomputed, commitment_32, 32)
End Process
